Variation in recruitment success was best explained by the number of days with rain during the entire nestling period (NumDays
  NestFull; 
  Table S1); this variable had substantially more support than the base model and models with other rainfall variables. When dividing the entire nestling period into two parts, there was more support for an effect of rain on juvenile survival during the early nestling period (NumDays
  Nest1) than during the second half (NumDays
  Nest2; 
  Table S1).
